definitions: designed to stop bullets from passing through or causing harm
impossible to find fault with; protected from any criticism or failure
examples: The president rode in a bulletproof limousine for security
Police officers wear bulletproof vests during dangerous operations
Her bulletproof argument convinced even the harshest critics
The lawyer prepared a bulletproof case with solid evidence

definitions: very good, first-rate, or excellent in quality or condition
examples: That's a bully idea for solving the problem
We had a bully time at the county fair

definitions: using strength or power to frighten or hurt weaker people
examples: His bullying behavior made younger students afraid of him
The company faced lawsuits over bullying tactics against competitors

definitions: of poor quality, not working properly, or disappointing
examples: He got a bum deal when buying that used car
My bum knee keeps me from playing sports

definitions: acting in a confused, awkward way and making many mistakes
examples: The bumbling detective accidentally solved the case through luck
His bumbling attempts at cooking resulted in a kitchen disaster

definitions: having many bumps, not smooth or level in texture
characterized by difficulties, setbacks, or irregular progress
examples: The bumpy road made the journey uncomfortable for passengers
We drove slowly over the bumpy dirt path
They had a bumpy start to their marriage but worked through it
The company experienced a bumpy transition to new management

definitions: able to float in water or rise in air; having low density
cheerful and confident; able to recover quickly from setbacks
examples: The buoyant life jacket kept the swimmer safely afloat
Cork is naturally buoyant and floats easily on water
Her buoyant personality brightened everyone's mood at the office
Despite setbacks, he remained buoyant about the company's future

definitions: carrying something heavy physically; weighed down with objects
having difficult responsibilities, worries, or problems that cause stress
examples: The burdened donkey struggled up the steep mountain path
Burdened shoppers carried heavy bags from the store
She felt burdened by her family's financial problems
The burdened CEO faced mounting pressure from shareholders

definitions: causing difficulty or worry; requiring great effort to handle or endure
examples: The burdensome regulations made it hard for small businesses to operate
Caring for elderly parents became burdensome without help

definitions: involving complicated official rules and processes that seem unnecessary and delay results
examples: The bureaucratic process for getting permits took several months
She got frustrated with the bureaucratic red tape at city hall

definitions: beginning to grow or increase rapidly; flourishing or expanding quickly
examples: The burgeoning tech industry attracted many young professionals
Her burgeoning interest in art led to painting classes

definitions: placed in the ground and covered with earth, especially after death
hidden from view; concealed beneath something or difficult to find
examples: The buried treasure remained hidden for three hundred years
Ancient buried cities were discovered by archaeologists
The important information was buried in the lengthy report
Her buried emotions finally surfaced during the therapy session

definitions: relating to theatrical entertainment that exaggerates or mocks something through humor
examples: The burlesque performance parodied famous political figures
His burlesque imitation of the teacher made students laugh

definitions: having a large, strong, heavy body; muscular and powerfully built
examples: The burly bouncer stood guard at the nightclub entrance
Burly lumberjacks competed in the log-rolling contest

definitions: damaged, injured, or marked by fire, heat, or chemicals
extremely tired from working too hard; experiencing physical or mental exhaustion
examples: The burned toast filled the kitchen with smoke
Her burned skin needed immediate medical attention
After months of overtime, employees felt completely burned out
The burned programmer took a long vacation to recover

definitions: polished by rubbing to make smooth and shiny; having a glossy finish
examples: The burnished copper kettle gleamed on the kitchen stove
Knights kept their burnished armor spotless for ceremonies

definitions: damaged or discolored by burning or exposure to excessive heat
examples: The burnt edges of the paper showed it survived a fire
She threw away the burnt cookies and started over

definitions: covered with or full of burrs, the prickly seed cases of plants
examples: The burry wool needed careful cleaning before spinning
Dogs returned from the field with burry coats

definitions: growing thickly with many branches or hair; having a full, dense appearance
examples: His bushy eyebrows nearly covered his eyes completely
The bushy tail helped the squirrel balance on branches

definitions: broken, ruined, or no longer working; having no money
examples: The bust television needed expensive repairs to work again
After bad investments, the company went completely bust

definitions: broken, cracked, or not functioning properly due to damage
caught in the act of wrongdoing; arrested or exposed
examples: The busted pipe flooded the basement with water
His busted phone screen made texting difficult
The teenagers got busted sneaking into the movie theater
Police busted the illegal gambling operation last night

definitions: full of energetic and noisy activity; crowded with people moving about
examples: The bustling marketplace sold fresh produce every morning
Tourists loved exploring the bustling streets of the city

definitions: having an appearance or manner traditionally associated with masculinity
examples: She preferred a butch style with short hair and leather jackets
The butch character challenged traditional gender roles

definitions: containing, tasting of, or covered with butter
having a smooth, soft texture or appearance similar to butter
examples: The buttery popcorn left grease on their fingers
Fresh buttery croissants filled the bakery with aroma
The leather had a buttery texture that felt luxurious
Sunset painted the sky in buttery yellow tones

definitions: closed or fastened using buttons; having buttons attached or done up
examples: His buttoned coat protected him from the cold wind
She wore a neatly buttoned blouse to the interview

definitions: supported or reinforced with buttresses or other structural supports
examples: The buttressed cathedral walls stood strong for centuries
Ancient buttressed bridges still carry traffic today

definitions: making a continuous humming or vibrating sound like bees
filled with excitement, activity, or animated conversation
examples: Buzzing bees moved from flower to flower collecting pollen
The buzzing fluorescent light needed to be replaced
The office was buzzing with rumors about the merger
The buzzing crowd waited eagerly for the concert

definitions: belonging to an earlier time; past and no longer existing
examples: They collected antiques from bygone eras of history
The museum displayed fashions from bygone days

definitions: relating to childbirth by surgical operation through the mother's abdomen
examples: The caesarean delivery was necessary for the baby's safety
She recovered quickly from her caesarean section surgery

definitions: carefully planned or intended to achieve a particular effect or result
determined by mathematical computation; worked out using arithmetic
examples: Her calculated risk in investing paid off handsomely
The politician made calculated statements to win voter support
The calculated distance between planets helped plan the mission
Engineers used calculated measurements for bridge construction

definitions: coldly planning to get what you want, often without caring about others
examples: Her calculating nature made coworkers distrust her motives completely
The calculating villain planned every detail of the scheme

definitions: carefully adjusted or marked for accurate measurement; precisely set to standard
examples: The calibrated scale gave exact measurements for the experiment
Pilots relied on calibrated instruments for safe navigation

definitions: having patches of different colors, especially describing cats with three colors
examples: The calico cat had orange, black, and white fur
She made curtains from calico fabric with floral prints

definitions: relating to decorative handwriting or the art of producing beautiful writing
examples: The calligraphic wedding invitations impressed all the guests
Ancient calligraphic manuscripts were displayed in the museum

definitions: showing cruel disregard for others; emotionally hardened and unfeeling
examples: His callous remarks hurt her feelings deeply
The callous treatment of workers led to protests

definitions: young and lacking experience or maturity; naive about the world
examples: The callow recruit made many mistakes during training
Her callow understanding of politics showed in debates

definitions: relating to calories or the energy value found in food and drinks
examples: The caloric content of fast food concerned health experts
Athletes tracked their daily caloric intake carefully

definitions: hidden by means of protective coloring or patterns that blend with surroundings
examples: The camouflaged soldiers were nearly invisible in the forest
Camouflaged cameras captured wildlife behavior without disturbance

definitions: deliberately exaggerated, artificial, or theatrical in an amusing way
examples: The campy horror movie became a cult classic
Her campy performance delighted the audience with its humor

definitions: having a bright yellow color like that of a canary bird
examples: She wore a canary dress that brightened the room
The canary paint made the kitchen feel sunny

definitions: decided not to happen; stopped from taking place as planned
examples: The cancelled flight left passengers stranded at the airport
Heavy rain caused the cancelled outdoor concert

definitions: affected by or relating to cancer; containing malignant cells that spread
examples: Doctors removed the cancerous tumor during surgery
Early detection of cancerous cells improves treatment outcomes

definitions: truthful and straightforward; frank in expressing opinions without hiding anything
examples: Her candid feedback helped improve the project significantly
The politician gave surprisingly candid answers during interviews

definitions: relating to or resembling dogs or members of the dog family
examples: The veterinarian specialized in canine diseases and treatments
His canine teeth were sharp and prominent

definitions: preserved in sealed metal containers for long-term storage
prepared in advance; lacking spontaneity or genuine feeling
examples: Canned vegetables lasted months in the pantry
The soup kitchen relied on canned goods donations
The comedian avoided canned jokes preferring spontaneous humor
His canned response didn't address the real question

definitions: relating to the practice of eating flesh of one's own species
examples: Some spiders display cannibalistic behavior after mating
The cannibalistic tribe was featured in horror stories

definitions: showing good judgment, especially in money or business matters; clever and careful
examples: The canny investor doubled her money in five years
His canny negotiations saved the company thousands

definitions: accepted as being accurate, authoritative, or part of established principles
examples: Shakespeare's plays are part of the canonical English literature
The canonical version of the software fixed previous bugs

definitions: officially declared to be a saint by the Catholic Church
examples: The canonised nun founded hospitals across the country
Medieval canonised figures attracted pilgrims to churches

definitions: officially declared to be a saint by the Catholic Church
examples: The canonized priest dedicated his life to helping the poor
Many canonized saints have churches named after them
